==English==

=== Etymology ===
Pejoritive. Colloquial. First used in the slave states of USA in mid 1800's 

=== Adjective ===
'''uppity'''

# a recently freed black person, or 
# any black person who acted ''"white"'' or ''"superior"''
# [[presumptuous]]

*Take that '''uppity''' [[nigger]] out of my place of business or I will kick him out.
*That old lady is '''uppity'''.
*I think you are one very '''uppity''' young man.

=== Adverb ===
'''uppity'''

*Stop acting '''uppity''' to your teacher.

